Go to Terminal and switch to your local project by typing the following command:

$ cd PATH_TO_YOUR_PROJECT_FOLDER

- If you have not added the Podfile from directory:
2. Once you are inside the project folder, type the command below to create/initialize your POD files:

$ pod init

//After running the “pod init” command you will notice that a Podfile was added to your project’s folder

3. Then open the Podfile with your text editor such as Sublime Text, Text Edit etc.. 
And add your dependencies under the “#Pods:

  pod 'GoogleMaps'
  pod 'GooglePlaces'
	pod 'Firebase/Firestore'
	pod 'Firebase/Storage'

4. Save and Close your Podfile.

- If you have added the Podfile from directory, than jump to this command:

5. Still inside your project’s folder, run the following command:

$ pod install

Once the installation is complete, you will get a confirmation message on the terminal and 
you will also notice that some files were automatically added to your project

6. Double click on the Xcode workspace to open the project

7. You can clean/re-build your project and run it.
